# DEPRECATED — this Dockerfile is no longer used.
#
# Originally built PyTorch from source with OpenBLAS to test whether it would
# outperform the pip wheel's statically-linked MKL on AWS Fargate.
#
# Benchmarks on Fargate's Intel Xeon Platinum (Cascade Lake, AVX-512) showed
# the opposite: MKL is ~26% faster than OpenBLAS for our sgemm workload
# (4096×256 @ 256×256). MKL also scales better — it saturates at 8 threads
# while OpenBLAS regresses at 16 threads.
#
# Results (c5.4xlarge, Xeon Platinum 8124M, 16 vCPU):
#   NumPy + MKL:      482 µs / 1104 GFLOPS
#   NumPy + OpenBLAS:  607 µs /  898 GFLOPS
#   PyTorch + MKL:    467 µs / ~1150 GFLOPS
#
# The main Dockerfile now uses Miniconda to install MKL-linked NumPy/SciPy,
# giving all backends access to MKL. PyTorch's pip wheel already bundles MKL.
#
# Kept for reference only. Use profiling/Dockerfile instead.
